# 5-Version Country Content System

Build a dynamic content system that serves US, UK, CA, AU, and General content across the entire site, driven by a global `CountryContext` with auto-detection.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Architecture shift:** The homepage (`/`) will dynamically render country-specific content based on the detected or selected country. The existing country pages (`/us`, `/uk`, `/au`, `/ca`) will redirect to `/?country=xx` rather than being separate pages. This means a single page component handles all 5 content versions. Alternatively, we can keep `/us` etc. as separate URLs but share the same component logic. **Which approach do you prefer?**

> [!WARNING]
> **Flag emojis on Windows:** Windows does not render national flag emojis (e.g. đź‡şđź‡¸ â†’ shows "US" text). The fix is to replace emoji flags with **small SVG flag images** bundled locally. This adds ~5 small files to `public/flags/`.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Country Context & Detection

#### [NEW] [CountryProvider.jsx](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\components\CountryProvider.jsx)
- React Context (`CountryContext`) wrapping the entire app
- On mount: reads `preferred-country` cookie â†’ sets active country
- If no cookie exists â†’ sets `"general"` (shows placeholder prompt)
- Exposes `{ country, setCountry }` to all components
- When user selects a country: sets cookie + updates context (no page reload)

#### [MODIFY] [layout.jsx](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\app\layout.jsx)
- Wrap `{children}` with `<CountryProvider>`

---

### Centralized Country Content

#### [NEW] [countryContent.js](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\lib\countryContent.js)
A single data file with **all content keyed by country code** (`us`, `uk`, `ca`, `au`, `general`). Each key contains:

| Section | Country-specific fields |
|---|---|
| **Hero** | `h1Line1`, `h1Line2`, `subtitle`, `flag`, `countryLabel` |
| **Stats** | `statsBanner` values (tailored per country) |
| **Trusted Software** | Country-relevant tools |
| **Software Columns** | Tools per country (QB for US, Xero for UK/AU, etc.) |
| **Compliance** | `complianceNote`, `complianceTools` |
| **CTA text** | Country-specific button labels and descriptions |
| **Contact email** | Country-specific email (us@, uk@, info@) |

Structural arrays (`processSteps`, `serviceCards`, `whyChooseUsCards`) remain shared since they are identical across all 5 versions.

#### [MODIFY] [siteData.js](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\lib\siteData.js)
- Keep shared structural data (processSteps, serviceCards, etc.)
- Remove country-specific content that moves to `countryContent.js`

---

### Flag Emoji Fix

#### [NEW] `public/flags/us.svg`, `uk.svg`, `au.svg`, `ca.svg`
- Small inline SVG flag icons (~1 KB each)
- Will render correctly on all platforms (Windows, Mac, iOS, Android)

#### [MODIFY] [countryData.js](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\lib\countryData.js)
- Add `general` entry: `{ code: 'general', name: 'Global', label: 'General', href: '/', flagSrc: null }`
- Replace `flag: 'đź‡şđź‡¸'` emoji strings with `flagSrc: '/flags/us.svg'` paths
- All components use `<img src={country.flagSrc}>` instead of emoji text

---

### Homepage (Dynamic Content)

#### [MODIFY] [page.jsx](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\app\page.jsx)
- Convert to a client component (required for context consumption)
- OR: keep as server + use a client wrapper component `<HomeContent />`
- Reads `country` from `useCountry()` context
- All sections render content from `countryContent[country]`
- When `country === 'general'`: shows neutral fallback content

#### [DELETE] [CountryLandingPage.jsx](file:///\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\amit25\clarivex-solution\components\CountryLandingPage.jsx)
- Its logic merges into the homepage since the homepage now handles all 5 versions
- The `/us`, `/uk`, `/au`, `/ca` routes will just set the country cookie and render the same component

#### [MODIFY] Country route pages ([us/page.jsx](file://wsl.localhost/Ubuntu/home/amit25/clarivex-solution/app/us/page.jsx), [uk/page.jsx](file://wsl.localhost/Ubuntu/home/amit25/clarivex-solution/app/uk/page.jsx), etc.)
- Each sets the country cookie server-side and renders `<HomeContent country="us" />`
- Or redirects to `/` with cookie set

